SIMPLE: flat-footed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flat-footed
<hw>Flat"-foot`ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a flat
foot, with little or no arch of the instep; suffering from fallen
arches.</def> <wns>[wns=3]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Firm-footed; determined.</def> <mark>[Slang,
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>clumsy; amateurish; pedestrian; unimaginative;
plodding; <as>as, <ex>flatfooted</ex> prose</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Without reservation; without evasion or compromise;
firm; <as>as, a <ex>flat-footed</ex> refusal; a <ex>flatfooted</ex>
denial</as>.</def> <wns>[wns=4]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> downright, forthright, foursquare, head-on,
straightforward.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>With feet flat on the ground; not tiptoe.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Unprepared and unable to react quickly; <as>as, the
new product caught their competitors <ex>flat-footed</ex></as>.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unready.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To catch (one) flatfooted</b></col> <cd>to catch (a
person) unprepared; to catch (a person) by surprise.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flathead</ent>⟦br⟧
